Colombian Stocks: Petrominerales Ltd., Interconexion Electrica

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-12T16:55:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/colombian-stocks-petrominerales-ltd-interconexion-electrica.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:02 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.7 percent to 13,315.95, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.8 percent to 1,619.58.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)  , a Medellin-based
electricity and road company, fell 0.7 percent to 11,880 pesos.
The company is interested in the  Portuguese government ’s planned
sale of shares in REN-Redes Energeticas Nacionais SA, Diario
Economico reported, without saying how it obtained the
information.  ISA has already contacted the Portuguese government about
its interest in REN, the operator of  Portugal ’s electricity and
gas networks, the Portuguese newspaper said.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
with production and exploration in Colombia, fell 3.8 percent to
53,100 pesos.  The company said due to blockades around its Corcel
facilities, it has been unable to restart production operations
on the Corcel and Guatiquia Blocks, according to a regulatory
filing today. As a result, production totaling over 30,000
barrels of oil per day has been shut-in, the filing said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
